text: b'The official Facebook page for the Office of the Assistant to President Morsy on Foreign Relations http://t.co/COkBHUWU'
b'For English-language news, like Egyptian Presidency Facebook page http://t.co/IEkhuVlF'
b'Follow @EgyPresidency for English-language news about the Egyptian Presidency.'
b'As an Egyptian; I know that there is no limit to what human beings can accomplish when they come together for a noble purpose #Morsi'
b'Humanity\xe2\x80\x99s universal heritage is a shared one that does not belong to a single color, creed or culture #Morsi'
b'We must never again find ways to whitewash or cover-up torture or abuse #Morsi'
b'Respect for human rights in all dimensions: faith, culture, social, economic, and political must be a key component in all our work #Morsi'
b'International organizations should respond and adapt to be more inclusive and democratic #Morsi'
b'We need to revisit how international economic systems operate #Morsi'
b'I am looking forward with big hope and see in horizon the peace that is based on justice, cooperation and equality #Morsi'
b'We also stand firmly against the use of violence in expressing objection to these obscenities #Morsi'
b'Egypt supports the freedom of expression.One that is not directed towards one specific religion or culture #Morsi'
b"The obscenities recently released as part of an organized campaign against Islam's prophet is unacceptable and requires a firm stand #Morsi"
b'We must act together in the face of extremism, discrimination, and incitement to hatred on the basis of religion or race #Morsi'
b'The vicious campaigns in some regions of the world against what Muslims and migrants hold sacred was violating their human rights #Morsi'
b'We expect from others, as they expect from us, that they respect our cultural particularities and religious points of reference #Morsi'
b'Egypt would like to stress that the international system will not get fixed as long as the application of double standards remains #Morsi'
b'I would like to emphasize the need for the UN to give special attention to supporting issues of women and youth #Morsi'
b'Revitalizing #UNGA and reforming the Security Council must remain high on the priority list we must tackle with seriousness #Morsi'
b'There is a need to work diligently to reform the international financial system based on justice, freedom and dignity #Morsi'
b'I assure you that Egypt continues to support its brothers and sisters in Africa #Morsi'
b'Today, we, as Africans, have to achieve for our continent a new set of ambitious goals #Morsi'
b"The world has the responsibility to support Africa's efforts, beyond mere promises #Morsi"
b'we also emphasize the right of all countries of the region to the peaceful use of nuclear energy within the framework of the NPT #Morsi'
b'The conference on achieving a  ME free of nuclear weapons and all other weapons of mass dest. should be held before end of 2012 #Morsi'
b'Egypt stresses the necessity of holding a conference on a  Middle East free of nuclear weapons and all other mass dest. weapons #Morsi'
b'People, esp. in our region, no longer tolerates the continued non-accession of any country to the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty #Morsi'
b'Today peoples of the region will not tolerate being deprived of their rights, whether by their own leaders or outside forces #Morsi'
b'I call upon all Members of this Assembly to support the efforts of the #Somali Government #Morsi'
b'#Sudan has made great sacrifices in its quest for peace and stability. But to be frank: it has not received the support it deserves #Morsi'
b'Our brothers and sisters in Sudan need, more than ever, your support #Morsi'
b'Egypt\xe2\x80\x99s is committed to work with its Arab brothers and sisters to reclaim our rightful position in the world #Morsi'
b'Egypt is also committed to supporting the mission of Al-Akhdar Al-Ibrahimi to Syria #Morsi'
b'I would like to emphasize that the initiative is open to all those who wish to positively contribute in resolving the Syrian crisis #Morsi'
b'We will continue to work to put an end to the suffering of the Syrian people #Morsi'
b'Syrian people, dear to our hearts, deserve to hope for a future of freedom and dignity #Morsi'
b'The blood that is shed in #Syria that is dear and near to us is far too valuable to continue to be shed day and night #Morsi'
b'The bloodshed in #Syria and the humanitarian crisis that has unfolded must be stopped #Morsi'
b'I assure you of Egypt full support to any course of action Palestine decides to follow in the United Nations #Morsi'
b'I call for immediate measures to put an end to colonization, settlement activities and alteration in identity of Jerusalem #Morsi'
b'It is disgraceful that settlement activities continue on the territories of Palestinians  #Morsi'
b'Our brothers and sisters in Palestine must also taste the fruits of freedom and dignity #Morsi'
b'The international legitimacy remains unable  until now to realize the hopes and aspirations of the Palestinian people  #Morsi'
b'Post-revolution Egypt is among the leading nations defending justice, truth, freedom, and dignity #Morsi'
b'The vision of the new Egypt that we strive to realize for our nation also constitutes the frame of action we present to the world #Morsi'
b'Today, every Egyptian shares a sense of self-confidence, which puts him/her on higher moral grounds #Morsi'
b'The headlines of president #Morsi speech in front of #UNGA coming to you in English shortly'
b'The revolutions of the Arab spring happened because people realized that they are the real source of power #Morsi'
b'We cannot ignore practices that are destroying our planet and claim we have good global governance #Morsi'
b'Egyptians are the ultimate guarantors of the success during the transition from dictatorship to democracy #Morsi'
b'Pres. #Morsi interview with Charlie Rose highlighting political future of Egypt, rev. in Syria and relations with US\n http://t.co/eEqAIbrv'
b'Our foreign policy now is based on mutual respect and shared interests - #Morsi'
b'We support the Palestinians in their quest for their rights - #Morsi'
b'Peace cannot be achieved in the region without the Palestinian people receiving their full rights and establishing their state - #Morsi'
b'We must stem the bloodshed in #Syria and the #Syrian regime must understand that it is operating outside of all laws and norms - #Morsi'
b'Our relations with Africa and the countries of the Nile basin are at the heart of our foreign policy - #Morsi'
b'I will only use my legislative authority in the narrowest of circumstances - #Morsi'
b'I took the August 12 decisions not to marginalize any institutions but rather as the expression of the will of the people - #Morsi'
b'I will uphold whatever the constitution dictates once the People endorse it - #Morsi'
b'I do not interfere in the writing of the constitution - #Morsi'
b'The ballot box is the arbiter and freedom of expression is guaranteed for all sides - #Morsi'
b'No political party, group, or current should fear another - #Morsi'
b'After the result, I felt overwhelmed by the responsibility and I prayed to Allah and put my faith in the Egyptian people - #Morsi'
b'We will have to work very hard until we can produce what we need. No one will do for us what we must do for ourselves - #Morsi'
b'We need some time, but we have many reasons for hope: resources and willpower. We will move together God willing to a better tomorrow-#Morsi'
b'The blood of the martyrs was the real fuel of the revolution and was the fuel behind all of the changes that came subsequently - #Morsi'
b'The coming tweets are the most important ideas highlighted by the HE president #Morsi'
b'Want to dedicate 1st tweet to martyrs of #jan25 revolution and brave #syrians... Muhammed #Morsi'
